---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import cliFlow from "../../../docs/assets/fieldwork-cli-flow.svg?url";
import pairingFlow from "../../../docs/assets/fieldwork-pairing.svg?url";
import mobileSession from "../../../docs/assets/fieldwork-mobile-session.svg?url";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Fieldwork"
  description="Open-source terminal handoff for any CLI: keep one PTY session alive on your laptop and continue it from iOS or Android."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Universal terminal handoff</p>
      <h1>Fieldwork</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Run any CLI on your laptop, leave the desk, and attach to that same live PTY
        session from iOS or Android. Shells, TUIs, REPLs, Claude Code, and Codex all
        keep their state in one daemon-owned session.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/install/">Install desktop CLI</a>
        <a class="button" href="/architecture/">Read architecture</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="terminal-scene" aria-label="Fieldwork session handoff preview">
      <div class="terminal-window">
        <div class="terminal-bar" aria-hidden="true"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
        <pre class="terminal-body"><code><span class="prompt">$</span> fieldwork new --dir ~/projects/api claude
created 018f1e...  claude · api

<span class="prompt">$</span> fieldwork ls
SESSION                         STATUS
claude · api                    Working
bash · fieldwork                Idle
vim · docs                      Attached

<span class="dim">phone attached over iroh</span>
Claude is waiting for input.
Continue with the release notes?

<span class="prompt">$</span> y</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="phone-window">
        <h2>Sessions</h2>
        <div class="session-row">
          <strong>claude · api</strong>
          <span>Awaiting input</span>
        </div>
        <div class="session-row">
          <strong>bash · fieldwork</strong>
          <span>Idle</span>
        </div>
        <div class="session-row">
          <strong>vim · docs</strong>
          <span>Attached</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band light">
    <div class="split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What ships in v1</p>
        <h2>One daemon. Many views. Raw PTY bytes.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="tile">
          <h3>Arbitrary commands</h3>
          <p>`bash`, `zsh`, `vim`, `htop`, `python`, `node`, `lazygit`, `claude`, and `codex` run as normal PTYs.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="tile">
          <h3>Warm reconnect</h3>
          <p>Clients replay from a byte offset when possible and fall back to a synthetic ANSI snapshot when stale.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="tile">
          <h3>Agent-aware push</h3>
          <p>Claude Code and Codex get first-class waiting-for-input state; unknown CLIs still hand off cleanly.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Flow</p>
        <h2>Pair once, then attach anywhere.</h2>
      </div>
      <ol class="flow">
        <li><span>Install `fieldwork`, then start the user daemon.</span></li>
        <li><span>Run `fw pair`, scan the QR code, and approve the device on desktop.</span></li>
        <li><span>Create sessions from the laptop. Mobile can list, attach, send input, resize, detach, and register push tokens.</span></li>
        <li><span>Push payloads contain only fixed text and opaque hashes; terminal content is fetched over the paired iroh channel after unlock.</span></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band light">
    <div class="split">
      <div class="page-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Product surfaces</p>
        <h2>Desktop install, explicit pairing, live mobile terminal.</h2>
        <p>
          These source-controlled captures mirror the v1 flows used in local smoke tests and release documentation.
          Store screenshots are still a release gate because they need signed physical-device builds.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-list">
        <img class="shot" src={cliFlow} alt="Fieldwork CLI install and session list" />
        <img class="shot" src={pairingFlow} alt="Fieldwork QR pairing with desktop approval" />
        <img class="shot" src={mobileSession} alt="Fieldwork mobile sessions and terminal attach" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Docs</p>
        <h2>Security and protocol details are public.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <a class="tile" href="/protocol/">
          <h3>Protocol</h3>
          <p>Contract version, framing, attach/replay, pairing, and push registration.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="tile" href="/architecture/">
          <h3>Architecture</h3>
          <p>Daemon, mobile core, transport, relay, persistence, and npm distribution.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="tile" href="/privacy/">
          <h3>Privacy</h3>
          <p>What stays local, what crosses iroh, and what push providers can see.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
